@{
    Layout = "_Layout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="page-header footer-page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <span class="section-tag-enhanced"><i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i> Security Desk</span>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>How Eventify Pro collects, processes, encrypts, and safeguards your personal, booking, and payment data.</p>
        
        <div class="page-header-meta">
            <span class="meta-item"><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Reading time: 6 mins</span>
            <span class="meta-item"><i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i> Last updated: June 1, 2026</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="content-page section enhanced-bg-glow">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="legal-layout-enhanced">
            
            <!-- Sticky Sidebar Table of Contents -->
            <aside class="legal-sidebar-enhanced">
                <div class="toc-header">
                    <i class="fas fa-list-ol"></i>
                    <span>Table of Contents</span>
                </div>
                <nav class="toc-list">
                    <a href="#introduction" class="toc-link active" data-toc>1. Introduction</a>
                    <a href="#collect" class="toc-link" data-toc>2. Information We Collect</a>
                    <a href="#use" class="toc-link" data-toc>3. How We Use Data</a>
                    <a href="#payments" class="toc-link" data-toc>4. Payment & Stripe Security</a>
                    <a href="#qr-security" class="toc-link" data-toc>5. QR Ticket Security</a>
                    <a href="#retention" class="toc-link" data-toc>6. Data Retention & Deletion</a>
                </nav>
            </aside>

            <!-- Comprehensive Legal Content Panel -->
            <div class="legal-panel-enhanced">
                
                <!-- Section 1: Introduction -->
                <section id="introduction" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>1. Introduction & Core Commitment</h2>
                    <p>Welcome to <strong>Eventify Pro</strong>. We are fully committed to protecting your privacy and securing your personal, financial, and booking data. This Privacy Policy details exactly how we manage accounts, compile ticketing information, secure QR codes, process payments, and moderate public feedback. By registering an account as an Administrator, Organizer, Attendee, or Scanner, or by purchasing tickets on our platform, you explicitly consent to the data collection and security practices outlined below.</p>
                    <div class="legal-callout-info">
                        <h4><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Quick Summary</h4>
                        <p>Eventify Pro does not sell your personal data. We utilize enterprise-grade encryption for all tickets and securely outsource credit card billing to Stripe. Your data is used exclusively to facilitate event organization, booking confirmations, and entrance verification.</p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 2: Information We Collect -->
                <section id="collect" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
                    <p>To operate a smart and reliable event management system, Eventify Pro collects the following categories of information depending on your assigned system role:</p>
                    
                    <ul class="legal-list">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Account Registration Data:</strong> When registering, we collect your full name, email address, password hashes, and user role. This is required to provision secure dashboards for Organizers, Attendees, and entrance Scanners.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Event Creation Metadata:</strong> For organizers, our database stores event details (titles, descriptions, capacities, locations, high-resolution banner images, dates, and custom ticket tiers VIP or Regular) that you publish for attendees to browse.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Attendee Booking Records:</strong> When you purchase tickets, our platform logs your booking ID, ticket count, selected ticket tier, total transaction amounts, purchase timestamps, and email delivery receipts.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>We also log general system interaction metrics, such as scanner check-in timestamps and system error logs to ensure high platform uptime and reliability during high-traffic events.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 3: How We Use Data -->
                <section id="use" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
                    <p>We process your data strictly to fulfill the essential functionalities of the Eventify Pro ecosystem:</p>
                    
                    <ul class="legal-list">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> <strong>Ticketing & Ticket Generation:</strong> To generate and transmit secure, mathematically signed QR tickets that authorize entry at event gates.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> <strong>Organizer Dashboard Analytics:</strong> To provide event organizers with real-time financial tracking, sales charts, attendee counts, and capacity warning notifications.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> <strong>Entrance Scanner Verification:</strong> To allow staff holding scanner roles to instantly check guests in, verifying QR validity against our database in under one second.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> <strong>Feedback & Moderation:</strong> To process user feedback submitted via our platform. Feedback is kept private in our backend until reviewed and approved by an administrator before appearing on the landing page.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 4: Payment & Stripe Security -->
                <section id="payments" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>4. Financial Processing & Stripe Billing Security</h2>
                    <p>All ticket transaction payments on Eventify Pro are processed using <strong>Stripe</strong>, one of the world's most secure and robust payment gateways. We prioritize credit card security by incorporating the following principles:</p>
                    <p><strong>PCI Compliance & Storage:</strong> Eventify Pro <strong>never stores, sees, or transmits full credit card details or CVVs</strong> on our servers. All card forms are securely tokenized and handled directly by Stripe in compliance with Payment Card Industry Data Security Standards (PCI-DSS) Level 1.</p>
                    <p>Stripe processes the attendee's name, email, card details, billing address, and transaction amount to prevent fraudulent transactions and authorize ticket bookings. Organizers receive their payouts directly through verified banking accounts linked securely to Stripe, shielding all sensitive information from third parties.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 5: QR Ticket Security -->
                <section id="qr-security" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>5. Cryptographic QR Ticket Security & Anti-Fraud Logs</h2>
                    <p>Our ticketing system is designed with state-of-the-art protection against counterfeiting and duplicate access attempts:</p>
                    <p><strong>QR Decryption:</strong> Every generated ticket has an encrypted cryptographic string corresponding to a unique database record. It cannot be guessed or brute-forced. When scanned, the scanning device sends this token to our servers for decryption and real-time database validation.</p>
                    <p><strong>Scan Timestamp Logging:</strong> To prevent attendees from printing and scanning multiple photocopies of a single ticket, our system records the exact scanner ID and timestamp the instant a guest passes entry. Subsequent scans trigger an immediate duplication alert, logging the unauthorized attempt details in the administrator dashboard to ensure complete venue gate security.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 6: Data Retention & Deletion -->
                <section id="retention" class="legal-section">
                    <h2>6. Data Retention, User Rights, & Deletion Requests</h2>
                    <p>You have full ownership of your data on Eventify Pro. You have the right to request access to your account details, edit your organizer profile, or delete your booking history:</p>
                    <ul class="legal-list">
                        <li><i class="fas fa-user-edit"></i> <strong>Profile Updates:</strong> You can edit your personal details, email, and preferences at any time from your account setting panels.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-trash-alt"></i> <strong>Account Deletion:</strong> If you request complete account deletion, our database will purge all personal records, passwords, and inactive tickets.</li>
                        <li><i class="fas fa-history"></i> <strong>Financial Transaction Retention:</strong> Please note that financial transaction ledgers and stripe payout records must be legally preserved for accounting, auditing, and tax compliance reasons according to international financial bookkeeping laws.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>If you have any inquiries about your data rights or wish to execute a data deletion request, please submit a request to our support representatives through the Help Center.</p>
                </section>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@section Scripts {
    <script>
        // Smooth Table of Contents Active State Highlighting
        const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.legal-section');
        const tocLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.toc-link');

        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            let current = '';
            sections.forEach(section => {
                const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                const sectionHeight = section.clientHeight;
                if (pageYOffset >= (sectionTop - 150)) {
                    current = section.getAttribute('id');
                }
            });

            tocLinks.forEach(link => {
                link.classList.remove('active');
                if (link.getAttribute('href') === `#${current}`) {
                    link.classList.add('active');
                }
            });
        });
    </script>
}
